sect.title: Wiring Fields Definition
sect.p: This document outlines the definitions of various fields used within the wiring data structure. It details the attributes and their meanings for standard parts used in wiring harnesses.

item.title: Part Number
item.p: Definition: The unique identifier for the conduit.

item.title: Alternative Part Number
item.p: Definition: An alternative identifier for the same conduit.

item.title: Manufacturer Code
item.p: Definition: The code identifying the manufacturer of the conduit.

item.title: Size
item.p: Definition: The physical size of the conduit.

item.title: Mass
item.p: Definition: The weight of the conduit.

item.title: Color
item.p: Definition: The color of the conduit.

item.title: Wall Thickness
item.p: Definition: The thickness of the conduit's wall.

item.title: Minimum Temperature
item.p: Definition: The lowest operating temperature the conduit can withstand.

item.title: Maximum Temperature
item.p: Definition: The highest operating temperature the conduit can withstand.

item.title: Functional Description Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing a more detailed functional description.

item.title: Illustration Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing an illustration of the conduit.

item.title: Part Number
item.p: Definition: The unique identifier for the identification sleeve.

item.title: Alternative Part Number
item.p: Definition: An alternative identifier for the same identification sleeve.

item.title: Manufacturer Code
item.p: Definition: The code identifying the manufacturer of the identification sleeve.

item.title: Length
item.p: Definition: The length of the identification sleeve.

item.title: Material
item.p: Definition: The material the identification sleeve is made from.

item.title: Mass
item.p: Definition: The weight of the identification sleeve.

item.title: Functional Description Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing a more detailed functional description.

item.title: Illustration Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing an illustration of the identification sleeve.

item.title: Part Number
item.p: Definition: The unique identifier for the wire material.

item.title: Alternative Part Number
item.p: Definition: An alternative identifier for the same wire material.

item.title: Manufacturer Code
item.p: Definition: The code identifying the manufacturer of the wire material.

item.title: Wire Type
item.p: Definition: The type of wire (e.g., stranded, solid).

item.title: Wire Gauge
item.p: Definition: The gauge of the wire.

item.title: Number of Cores
item.p: Definition: The number of conductors within the wire.

item.title: Size
item.p: Definition: The physical size of the wire.

item.title: Mass
item.p: Definition: The weight of the wire per unit length.

item.title: Color
item.p: Definition: The color of the wire insulation.

item.title: Outer Jacket Color
item.p: Definition: The color of the outer jacket (if applicable).

item.title: Outer Diameter
item.p: Definition: The overall diameter of the wire.

item.title: Resistance
item.p: Definition: The direct current resistance of the wire.

item.title: Voltage
item.p: Definition: The maximum operating voltage.

item.title: Amperage
item.p: Definition: The maximum current carrying capacity.

item.title: Minimum Temperature
item.p: Definition: The lowest operating temperature.

item.title: Maximum Temperature
item.p: Definition: The highest operating temperature.

item.title: Screen Count
item.p: Definition: The number of shields or screens.

item.title: Coaxial Cable Flag
item.p: Definition: Indicates if the wire is a coaxial cable.

item.title: Tri-axial Cable Flag
item.p: Definition: Indicates if the wire is a tri-axial cable.

item.title: Impedance
item.p: Definition: The AC impedance of the wire (typically for cables).

item.title: Frequency
item.p: Definition: The frequency at which impedance or attenuation are measured.

item.title: Attenuation
item.p: Definition: The signal loss per unit length at a given frequency.

item.title: Functional Description Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing a more detailed functional description.

item.title: Illustration Reference
item.p: Definition: Reference to a document containing an illustration of the wire material.
